        "Overriding the Build"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Normally, the CLI runs a hard-coded set of commands based on the project type. For example, the standard web asset build for Angular projects is ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ng run app:build"
      ],
      ". The web asset build can be overridden and ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic build"
      ],
      " can continue to be used by utilizing the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic:build"
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://docs.npmjs.com/misc/scripts"
        },
        "npm script"
      ],
      ". Similarly, the dev server can be overridden by using the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic:serve"
      ],
      " npm script."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Pay close attention to the flags supplied to the script by the Ionic CLI. Irregularities may occur if options are not respected, especially for livereload on devices."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "command-options"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#command-options"
        },
        "Command Options"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Command options can be expressed with environment variables. They are normally set with ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "--opt=value"
      ],
      " syntax. The naming of these environment variables follows a pattern: start with ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "IONIC_CMDOPTS_"
      ],
      ", add the command name (replacing any spaces with underscores), add the option name (replacing any hyphens with underscores), and then uppercase everything. Boolean flags (command-line options that don't take a value) can be set to ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "1"
      ],
      " or ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "0"
      ],
      ". Strip the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "--no-"
      ],
      " prefix in boolean flags, if it exists (",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "--no-open"
      ],
      " in ionic serve can be expressed with ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "IONIC_CMDOPTS_SERVE_OPEN=0"
      ],
      ", for example)."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "For example, the command options in ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "ionic cordova run ios -lc --livereload-port=1234 --host=0.0.0.0"
      ],
      " can also be expressed with this series of environment variables:"
